#eNCA's Heidi Giokos has more details. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Joe Phaahla says the new COVID-19 draft regulations won't go on forever. He says there will be amendments as the situation changes. READ: Phaahla dismisses claims government is micro-managing nation The draft regulations are aimed at dealing with Covid-19 in the absence of the national state of disaster. The public has until 24 April to have their say on the regulations.